# T-2387 — Waker-liveness canary (G-069 shipped≠live guard for the comms rail)
# Source of truth: /opt/termlink/.context/cron/waker-liveness-canary.crontab (git-tracked)
# Installed to:    /etc/cron.d/termlink-waker-liveness-canary (USER field syntax — do NOT load into a user crontab)
#
# arc-004 push-wake shipped and was live-proven (T-2388), but "0 wakers
# fleet-wide" sat dark for weeks with nothing firing (T-2380 E4/F3). This daily
# canary fires (exit 1, log entry) when the host looks reachable but cannot be
# push-woken:
#   (a) a LIVE agent-presence listener WITHOUT pty_session (unwakeable — peers
#       can DM it durably but nothing rings its PTY, T-2380 breakpoint #2);
#   (b) a local be-reachable*.state whose pushwaker_pid is dead (waker died
#       silently after arming — clean stop removes the state file);
#   (c) rail-dark (--expect-armed, declared for .107 where agents ARE expected
#       armed): ZERO LIVE listeners carry pty_session at all — the literal
#       G-069 "0 wakers" state.
# Empty log = healthy. /canaries auto-discovers this log + heartbeat.
#
# Operator action on firing: relaunch the named agent(s) through the T-2388
# launcher — `bash scripts/tl-claude.sh start --reachable --agent-id <name> --
# --resume` (running headless claudes cannot be retrofitted, PL-237 — arm at
# relaunch); dead wakers re-arm via `bash scripts/be-reachable.sh start`.
# Ad-hoc check: `bash scripts/check-waker-liveness-freshness.sh --expect-armed`.
SHELL=/bin/bash
PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin

# Daily at 07:53 UTC — offset from the :13/:17/:23/:43 canaries and the
# :23/:53 early-morning heartbeats (nearest neighbours: 07:43 task-finalization,
# 08:33 fleet-binary).
53 7 * * * root cd /opt/termlink && bash scripts/check-waker-liveness-freshness.sh --expect-armed --quiet >> .context/working/.waker-liveness-canary.log 2>&1
